Legend has it that the heaven is located above the clouds, but it is not. The real heaven is located in the underworld and exists very high above the underworld. It was originally the place where the dead go, but the human beings who have not yet passed away can also become heavenly beings. The living who become heavenly beings abandon the earthly emotions and six desires, and naturally abandon the desire to live in the earthly world. This means that although human beings who have become celestial beings are still alive, they have become existences that are essentially the same as the dead.

Even if they are celestial maidens, there are many kinds of celestial beings such as Tathagata and flying people. The life of the inferior celestial maidens is by no means rich, especially after Gensokyo has become like it is now, and even some celestial maidens are even poorer than humans. Life in the celestial world is surprisingly hierarchical, and only a few celestial maidens live in prosperity.

In Gensokyo, no matter whether it is inserting the key stone or pulling out the key stone, only the Hinamen can do it. If the main stone is pulled out, the foundation of the entire Gensokyo will be shaken.

The so-called spiritual enrichment is not tenderness or tolerance. It is the state of having no desires and being content with the status quo, that is, knowing "satisfaction". Everyone is too contented, and only eats peaches all day long. But I know it myself. I am not satisfied. I also know that cooking should have various tricks. I have never left the birthplace of Tenkai before, and I once visited Gensokyo while traveling around. It turns out that everyone is also eating a lot of things other than peaches. After all, it's rare for a person with good taste like me to come here, so I can't forget the food I ate in the village at that time. Wouldn't it be nice for Tianren to try sushi or meat? Although the wine was drunk from the beginning. All in all, I really want to eat mozzarella cheese and peach salad now.
